1. *Katkad* se osećam usamljeno. (Sometimes I feel lonely.)
2. Želim da *katkad* odem na more. (I want to sometimes go to the sea.)
3. Oni dolaze *katkad*. (They come sometimes.)
4. *Katkad* je potrebno napraviti pauzu. (Sometimes it is necessary to take a break.)
5. *Katkad* ne znam šta da kažem. (Sometimes I don't know what to say.)
6. *Katkad* mi nedostaje dom. (Sometimes I miss home.)
7. Čitam knjige *katkad*. (I read books sometimes.)
8. *Katkad* je teško doneti odluku. (Sometimes it's hard to make a decision.)
9. *Katkad* želim da promenim svoj život. (Sometimes I want to change my life.)
10. *Katkad* se pitam šta bi bilo da sam izabrao drugačiji put. (Sometimes I wonder what would have happened if I had chosen a different path.)

(Note: In Serbian, the word "katkad" means "sometimes" or "occasionally". It is usually used as an adverb and placed at the beginning or in the middle of a sentence.)